2
· BOQ Preparation & Estimation
· - Prepare detailed and itemized Bill of Quantities (BOQs) for interior, civil, electrical, HVAC, and finishing works.
· - Extract quantities from AutoCAD drawings and validate design inputs from consultants and project teams.
· - Benchmark costs based on recent projects, supplier quotes, and market analysis.
· - Coordinate with design and project managers for scope confirmation and cost validations.
· Sourcing & Vendor Management
· - Identify, evaluate, and empanel suppliers, contractors, and OEMs across key categories (civil, MEP, furniture, finishes, etc.).
· - Build and maintain a robust vendor database with updated rate cards and performance ratings.
· - Develop regional supplier networks to ensure competitive pricing and timely delivery.
· Tendering & Bid Management
· - Prepare and float RFPs / RFQs through both online and offline channels.
· - Conduct reverse auctions, bid evaluations, and comparative statements (CS sheets).
· - Analyze technical and commercial submissions and coordinate clarifications with bidders.
· - Negotiate pricing, delivery terms, and payment milestones to achieve cost efficiency.
· Cost Control & Contracting
· - Prepare cost summaries, rate analysis, and procurement trackers.
· - Ensure all procurement aligns with approved project budgets and timelines.
· - Support preparation of Purchase Orders, Work Orders, and Subcontract Agreements.
· - Work closely with finance and PM teams for vendor payments, retention, and closure documentation.
· Governance & Reporting
· - Maintain transparency through structured bid documentation and approval workflows.
· - Track procurement status against project schedules and update MIS dashboards weekly.
· - Drive cost savings, compliance, and performance benchmarking across all procurement categories.
