Technical And Functional Competencies

 Negotiations Excellence: Uses tools and methods effectively in negotiations to achieve Cummins’ stakeholder objectives and balanced contract terms.
 Procurement Systems & Tools: Demonstrates proficiency with procurement applications (e.g., PO, payment, engineering release, and quality systems) and is capable of troubleshooting data issues, generating ad-hoc reports, and supporting system implementations.
 Supplier Performance Management: Monitors, evaluates, and improves supplier performance through structured metrics, cross-functional collaboration, and continuous improvement processes.
 Supplier Capacity & Contract Management: Ensures suppliers can meet Cummins’ production and aftermarket demands while managing contractual performance and obligations.
 Supply Base Risk Management: Identifies, analyzes, and mitigates supplier risks to ensure continuity of supply, margin protection, and reputation management.
 Manufacturing Knowledge: Understands manufacturing processes to implement relevant procurement decisions effectively.
 Data Analytics: Applies data analysis, visualization, and reporting to extract meaningful business insights that drive data-driven decisions.
 Procurement Ethics & Compliance: Adheres to ethical sourcing practices and ensures that support Cummins’ operational and strategic goals.

Behavioral Competencies

 Action Oriented: Approaches new challenges with urgency, energy, and enthusiasm.
 Collaborates: Builds strong partnerships and works collaboratively to meet shared objectives.
 Communicates Effectively: Delivers clear, concise, and audience-specific communication across stakeholders.
 Values Differences: Recognizes and appreciates diverse perspectives and cultural contributions within the organization.
 Problem Solving: Uses systematic analysis and industry-standard methodologies to identify root causes and implement sustainable solutions.

Experience And Technical Expertise

Strong analytical skills with a solid understanding of supply chain management principles.
Proficiency in Power BI and Advanced Excel for data-driven decision-making and reporting.
Demonstrated adaptability to new procurement tools and technologies.
Proven experience in supplier management, sourcing analytics, or supply continuity support.
Excellent English communication and stakeholder management skills.
